  "notes": "Greater Porto suburban dialect with unique vowel breaking (Brechung): stressed mid vowels develop centering offglide — [ɛ͡ɐ, ɔ͡ɐ, e͡ɐ, o͡ɐ, ẽ͡ɐ̃]. Also attested in Portalegre (Crato). Backed rounded nasal [ɒ̃] for /ɐ̃/. Retroflex lateral [ɭ] in clusters.",
